Corsham man arrested on suspicion of drug-driving in Swindon
Updated 4:11pm Monday 2nd May 2016 in
A MAN who chose the wrong car to pull out in front of has been charged with drug-driving.
The incident happened on Thursday, April 28, at around midday when a police officer was forced to stop his vehicle as a VW Polo pulled out in front of him in Whitehead Street.
A police spokesman said: "The officer stopped the car and spoke to the driver, and suspected the driver had been using cannabis.
"A roadside drug swipe was carried out and showed positive.
"The 23-year-old man from Corsham was arrested on suspicion of drug driving and driving without a licence and insurance. He's been released on unconditional bail."
